tldr: The agent reviewed and significantly enhanced a sleep questionnaire
  application, implementing critical features like a tiredness severity scale,
  COMISA and insufficient sleep syndrome detection, weighted EDS scoring,
  comprehensive CSV export, and detailed medical/mental health history sections.
  The updates provide more accurate diagnostics and actionable user reports.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, aiming to validate existing features against a detailed
  specification and identify any missing functionalities. The agent conducted a
  thorough analysis, pinpointing several key areas for improvement.
  Subsequently, the agent systematically implemented all identified
  enhancements. This included integrating a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with
  critical safety warnings, developing detection logic for COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and enriching the report generation with weighted
  EDS scoring and a dedicated resources section featuring external links.
  Furthermore, the CSV export functionality was significantly expanded to
  capture all questionnaire data, and new sections were added to screen for
  pain-related issues, chronic fatigue, and to collect detailed medical and
  mental health history. The implementation involved extensive modifications
  across types, validations, UI components, and reporting logic, ensuring a more
  robust and diagnostically capable application.
